</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB98:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB98"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              98-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Assembly
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">January 05, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Assembly
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">April 24, 2025</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 98</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Jackson<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>January 07, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">An act to add Section 14673.13 to the Government Code, relating to state property.</span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 98, as amended, Jackson.
                          State property: City of Moreno Valley.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law authorizes the Director of General Services to execute grants to real property belonging to the state in the name and upon behalf of the state, whenever the sale or exchange of real property is authorized or contemplated by law, if no other state agency is specifically authorized and directed to execute the grants.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill<font color="#B30000"><strike> would</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> would, subject to specified requirements,</i></font> require the director to quitclaim to the City of Moreno Valley, at no cost to the city, all interests of the state in<font color="#B30000"><strike> 10</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
			 11</i></font> specified parcels of land located in the City of Moreno Valley that consist mainly of undeveloped open-space land. The bill would require the City of Moreno Valley to use the land to conduct wildfire mitigation to ensure fire protection for residents and businesses, to increase open-space<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and outdoor recreational</i></font> opportunities, and any other similar use the City of Moreno Valley deems necessary. The bill would exempt the land from specified provisions of law governing the disposal of surplus state<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and local</i></font> real property.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would make legislative findings and declarations as to the necessity of a special statute for the City of<font color="#B30000"><strike> Moreno.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
			 Moreno Valley.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would make legislative findings and declarations related to a gift of public funds.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.26721171339476246"><div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(a) The Legislature finds and declares all of the following:</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) The State Fire Marshal is required to classify areas in the state into fire hazard severity zones. Certain state-owned parcels, however, fall within local responsibility areas as designated by the State Board of Forestry and Fire Protection. The parcels addressed in this act have been identified as local responsibility areas and are located within a very
				high fire hazard severity zone.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The City of Moreno Valley seeks to perform annual wildfire mitigation activities and inspections on these parcels, consistent with the practices applied to other properties within the city, and to expand recreational and outdoor space amenities for public use.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) These parcels are situated in close proximity to schools, residential neighborhoods, a college campus, and a fire station, and currently lack regular maintenance and wildfire prevention measures.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) The City of Moreno Valley has made a commitment that once the parcels in this act are quitclaimed to the city, the city will obtain the best Public Protection Classification, more commonly known as an ISO Rating, through wildfire mitigation efforts, in order to reduce insurance premiums in that area.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5) On or around 1989, Assessor’s Parcel Numbers 304-020-008 and 304-280-006 were conveyed to the City of Moreno Valley and, subsequently, deeded from the city to the state at no cost. The original transferor, who continues to operate within the city, has expressed a willingness to provide testimony in support of returning these parcels and the neighboring nine parcels to the city to fulfill the intent of the original conveyance and to enable the development of extensive public open-space trails.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) It is, therefore, the intent of the Legislature to facilitate the transfer of these parcels to the City of Moreno Valley to promote enhanced wildfire mitigation, public safety, including improved Public Protection Classification ratings, and community access to recreational open space.</div></i></font></div></div><div id="s20.8192320754736206"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>SECTION 1.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 2.</i></font></h3> Section 14673.13 is added to the Government Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_7EE2F7D3-8FEB-4CEE-8347-4D5195C13CB9"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">14673.13.</h6> (a) <font color="#B30000"><strike>The </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Subject to the requirements in subdivision (d), the </i></font>Director of General Services shall quitclaim to the City of Moreno Valley, at no cost to the city, all interests of the state in the following<font color="#B30000"><strike> 10</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> 11</i></font> parcels of land located within the City of Moreno Valley that consist mainly of undeveloped open-space land, including mountains and hills:</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 304-020-008.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 304-280-009.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-030-004.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(4)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-030-006.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(5)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-030-008.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(6)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-030-009.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(7)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-030-010.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(8)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-030-013.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(9)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-030-014.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(10)<span class="EnSpace"/>APN: 308-050-008.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) APN: 304-020-008, consisting of 695.29 acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) APN: 304-280-006, consisting of 107.48 acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) APN: 304-280-009, consisting of 1.94 acre.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) APN: 308-030-004, consisting of 2.99 acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5) APN: 308-030-006, consisting of 84.25 acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(6) APN: 308-030-008, consisting of 33.24 acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(7) APN: 308-030-009, consisting of 162.32 acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(8) APN: 308-030-010, consisting of 90.60 acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(9) APN: 308-030-013, consisting of 4.11
						acres.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(10) APN: 308-030-014, consisting of 0.84 acre.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(11) APN: 308-050-008, consisting of 79.15 acres.</div></i></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) The City of Moreno Valley shall use the land to conduct wildfire mitigation to ensure fire protection for residents and businesses, to increase open-space<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and outdoor recreational</i></font> opportunities, and any other similar use the City of Moreno Valley deems necessary.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) The parcels of land identified in this section are<font color="#B30000"><strike> not subject to Section 11011.1.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						exempt from Section 11011.1 and Article 8 (commencing with Section 54220) of Chapter 5 of Part 1 of Division 2 of Title 5.</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(d) The Director of General Services shall quitclaim a parcel of land listed in subdivision (a) only if all of the following requirements are met:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) The parcel is located in a very high fire hazard severity zone, as identified by the State Fire Marshal pursuant to Section 51178.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The parcel, or any part of the parcel, is located within two miles of critical infrastructure.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) The parcel is designated as being in a local responsibility area and the City of Moreno Valley has responsibility for fire
						prevention and suppression.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(e) For purposes of this section, “critical infrastructure” includes residential housing, schools, water towers, power facilities, transportation systems, and public safety facilities.</div></i></font></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s30.30632700442230487"><div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>SEC. 2.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 3.</i></font></h3> The Legislature finds and declares that a special statute is necessary and that a general statute cannot be made applicable within the meaning of Section 16 of Article IV of the California Constitution because of the unique conditions in the City of Moreno Valley that make it vulnerable to potential wildfires, and the need to mitigate those threats.</div></div></div><div id="s40.7593969274988733"><div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>SEC. 3.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 4.</i></font></h3> The Legislature finds and declares that the addition of Section 14673.13 to the Government Code by this act serves a public purpose of promoting necessary wildfire mitigation to benefit residents and businesses located in areas vulnerable to wildfires and does not constitute a gift of public funds within the meaning of Section 6 of Article XVI of the California Constitution.</div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
